Randy Pierce lost his sight when he was 22 years old from a neurological disease that left him in a wheelchair . 
  He left his wheelchair in 2006 and has since climbed all 48 mountains in New Hampshire and run 30 road races with his guide dog Quinn  . 
  Pierce was one of only 10 percent of competitors to successfully complete the 'King of the Swingers' obstacle at a Tough Mudder competition in California last week . 
  He is preparing to run the Boston Marathon on April 20 . 
 